Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Cut half the @tortilla{2} into triangles (like pizza slices). Place on a lined #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} and toss to coat.

Arrange in a single layer (use two trays if necessary).

Bake in the oven until crispy and golden, ~{6-8%minutes} (Keep an eye on them so they don't burn).

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Roughly chop the @tomato{2}(roughly chopped) into small chunks.

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and chopped) into small pieces.

Quarter the @lime{1%whole}. Halve the @chilli{1%whole} and discard the core and seeds. Finely chop.

Slice the @avocado{2}(sliced lengthways). Twist and pull each half apart. Remove the pit and scoop the flesh out into a #bowl{}.

Mash the avocado with a #fork{} then add the onion, tomatoes, garlic and chilli (use less if you don't like spice).

Season to taste with salt, pepper and lime juice.

Serve up with the tortilla chips and any remaining lime wedges alongside.